parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbocharger can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded in hazardous situations.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the vehicle loses power
the turbocharger makes a loud whistling sound
the engine shutters or idles roughly
the check engine warning light illuminates
the vehicle is unable to accelerate
the vehicle stalls in traffic
the oil low light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil separator can cause the engine to run rough, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine runs rough
the oil separator makes a loud whistling sound
the vehicle is unable to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbocharger can cause the engine to stall or die, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls or dies while driving
loss of power
engine failure
car dies while in traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rough shifting of the transmission can cause a loss of control, leading to accidents or near-misses, and can also cause excessive wear on the transmission and other components.
symptoms: The transmission shifts roughly
vibration when shifting gears
dynamic mode causes rough shifting
driver's seat badges move back and forth.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The vehicle does not stop when the brake pedal is pushed
the vehicle vibrates violently when braking
the brakes shudder or pulse
the vehicle's speed is difficult to control when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration of the brake pedal can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The brake pedal vibrates violently when braking
the vehicle shudders or pulses when braking
the brakes make a loud noise when applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system computer can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The brake system computer does not record necessary failure codes
the brake system computer does not diagnose brake system failures.
